history.content: IB 131 and 131L are separate classes, so taking just 131 should give you 3 units of tech elective credit.

If I want to take a science class for a technical elective (Like INTEGBI 131, for example) do I have to take both 131 and 131L for the class to count as technical elective credit? Thanks! 

EDIT: Also, the degree requirements page says "All technical upper division undergraduate and graduate courses in integrative biology"; how do I tell if a course is a "technical" upper division course?
